<title>|xue and his father-in-law</title>
<summary>|xue pours water on his sleeping wife and she curses him. His wife takes a fire-stick and beats his forehead and |xue runs off to another place where he sleeps on the ground. At sunrise the wife&apos;s father looks for |xue, calling for him as he goes. |xue rises up and his father-in-law gives him food to eat. |xue goes with his father-in-law to his house where |xue&apos;s wife waits. She says that he had resembled many different things while he was gone and that she had seen him. He had been a man at sunset and a lizard at sunrise. She warns him that he will get killed by another man when he goes in this form into another country.</summary><comments>1) p.9340v: the names for the hunters of both large and small game, 2) p.9347v: see <i>|xue becomes !naxane</i>, 3) p.9348v: see <i>|xue as tchaxa</i>, 3) This story is found in Book XI &amp; XII-5</comments><date>20 â€“ 23 February 1880</date><storypages>9335-9349</storypages><category>Transformation</category><author>!nanni (XI)</author><author>Tamme (XII)</author><keyword><kw>|xue</kw><subkw>and his father-in-law</subkw></keyword>
